data.name: city
data.description: Only include locations that are completely or partly within the given city. The parameter's value must be a valid 3taps city code.

data.name: country
data.description: Only include locations that are completely or partly within the given country. The parameter's value must be a valid 3taps country code.

data.name: county
data.description: Only include locations that are completely or partly within the given county. The parameter's value must be a valid 3taps county code.

data.name: level
data.description: The desired location level.  The following location levels are currently supported: country, state, metro, region, county, city, locality, zipcode

data.name: locality
data.description: Only include locations that are completely or partly within the given locality. The parameter's value must be a valid 3taps locality code.

data.name: max_lat
data.description: If these parameters are supplied, only locations which are completely or partially enclosed by the given lat/long bounding box will be returned

data.name: max_long
data.description: If these parameters are supplied, only locations which are completely or partially enclosed by the given lat/long bounding box will be returned

data.name: metro
data.description: Only include locations that are completely or partly within the given metro area. The parameter's value must be a valid 3taps metro area code.

data.name: min_lat
data.description: If these parameters are supplied, only locations which are completely or partially enclosed by the given lat/long bounding box will be returned

data.name: min_long
data.description: If these parameters are supplied, only locations which are completely or partially enclosed by the given lat/long bounding box will be returned

data.name: region
data.description: Only include locations that are completely or partly within the given region. The parameter's value must be a valid 3taps region code.

data.name: state
data.description: Only include locations that are completely or partly within the given state. The parameter's value must be a valid 3taps state code.

description: The 3taps Reference API provides information about the data sources, categories and locations available within the 3taps system. This information can be used by external systems to do things such as displaying a pick-list of available categories, translating location codes into location names, etc.
